tandard interpretation of General Relativity, in which geometry determines gravity. 8. Contemporary physics undermines an objection to discrete aether based on scale invariance, but does not offer much positive support.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEther (Space) 0aEther (Space). 0aSpace and timexElectronic books. 0aSpace and time. 4aOntologie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aWissenschaftstheorie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY 2013z978311031732908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE 2013z9783110317312oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2013z978311033120208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2013z9783110331196oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311032517140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110325928zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110325928zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110325928/original  a978-3-11-031732-9 E-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY 2013b2013  a978-3-11-033120-2 eBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DONb201